WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.680
Today we are going to talk about a topic that everyone may have a sense of.

2
00:00:03.680 --> 00:00:11.240
When you work with AI, do you have a feeling that you are just using it and not really working with it?

3
00:00:11.240 --> 00:00:16.840
In today's content, we are going to talk about how to master the so-called tail art.

4
00:00:16.840 --> 00:00:21.600
Turn AI from a tool to your real strategic partner.

5
00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:24.120
Yes, this is where the question is, right?

6
00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:28.040
Many of us are thinking every day about how to hand things over to AI

7
00:00:28.040 --> 00:00:29.920
so that it can really help,

8
00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:34.040
not make more trouble for me on the contrary.

9
00:00:34.040 --> 00:00:36.200
This is really a big question.

10
00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:39.960
But there is an opinion here that I think may surprise you.

11
00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:41.440
Look at what this sentence says.

12
00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:46.320
It says that the timing of good tail art has actually nothing to do with AI.

13
00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:49.000
The key is your own professional knowledge.

14
00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:50.640
Hey, this is interesting.

15
00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:55.480
After a long time, the key is not the AI technology itself, but ourselves.

16
00:00:55.480 --> 00:00:56.760
What the hell is this?

17
00:00:56.760 --> 00:00:58.160
Let's take a look.

18
00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:00.640
Okay, how do we understand this?

19
00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:03.160
In fact, we can look at it as a framework.

20
00:01:03.160 --> 00:01:06.040
It's the so-called AI tail art three pillars.

21
00:01:06.040 --> 00:01:09.560
With this structure, we can understand this concept step by step.

22
00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:13.280
These three pillars are actually linked together.

23
00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.680
The first one is called problem awareness.

24
00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:19.960
The white line is that you have to figure out what you want to do first.

25
00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:22.160
Then the second one is platform awareness.

26
00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:26.400
You have to understand what weapons you have and how powerful they are.

27
00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:28.640
Finally, it's the mission tail.

28
00:01:28.640 --> 00:01:31.720
That is, how smart to divide the work.

29
00:01:31.720 --> 00:01:33.440
Sounds like it's not hard, right?

30
00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:35.240
But the devil is hidden in the details.

31
00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:36.920
Let's take a look one by one.

32
00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:38.960
Okay, let's take a look at the first step.

33
00:01:38.960 --> 00:01:40.960
Start from yourself.

34
00:01:40.960 --> 00:01:42.240
You might think it's weird.

35
00:01:42.240 --> 00:01:43.800
Isn't it talking about AI?

36
00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:45.720
How could it start from yourself?

37
00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:47.320
That's the point.

38
00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:50.440
What is this so-called problem awareness?

39
00:01:50.440 --> 00:01:54.200
To be honest, before you open any AI tool,

40
00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:58.120
you have to figure out the entire blueprint in your head.

41
00:01:58.120 --> 00:01:59.320
What is your goal?

42
00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:02.080
What things do you need to achieve your goal?

43
00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:03.800
It's kind of like building a house.

44
00:02:03.800 --> 00:02:06.000
You have to have a design picture in your hand.

45
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:09.000
Otherwise, no matter how hard you look for an AI worker,

46
00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:12.800
he won't be able to build the house you want, right?

47
00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:15.600
So how do you train this problem awareness?

48
00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:16.760
It's actually very simple.

49
00:02:16.760 --> 00:02:20.560
It's just that you stop and take a deep breath.

50
00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:22.400
Then ask yourself a few questions.

51
00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:24.960
For example, what exactly do I want to accomplish?

52
00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:27.400
How does this project work?

53
00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:28.680
And most importantly,

54
00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:33.800
what parts of the project do I need to use my expertise to make critical decisions?

55
00:02:33.800 --> 00:02:35.440
Think about these questions first.

56
00:02:35.440 --> 00:02:39.040
The foundation for your cooperation with AI is the real answer.

57
00:02:39.040 --> 00:02:39.880
So you see,

58
00:02:39.880 --> 00:02:41.560
this goes back to what we just said.

59
00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:44.080
Those who really use AI well,

60
00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:47.200
they are actually experts in their own field first.

61
00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:49.880
Then they are the messengers of AI.

62
00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:52.520
Don't forget that your own professional knowledge

63
00:02:52.520 --> 00:02:56.400
is the biggest and most irreplaceable weapon in your hands.

64
00:02:56.400 --> 00:03:01.160
OK, so the first step is to figure out your own goal first.

65
00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:03.400
What about after the goal is clear?

66
00:03:03.400 --> 00:03:04.160
The second step,

67
00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:09.800
let's take a look at what tools you have in your armory.

68
00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:10.360
This step,

69
00:03:10.360 --> 00:03:12.760
we call it platform awareness.

70
00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:14.400
Its meaning is actually very simple.

71
00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:16.960
You don't have to become a super strong engineer.

72
00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:20.360
But you have to be like a great chef.

73
00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:25.200
A good chef will be very clear about which knife and which pot he has in his kitchen.

74
00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:27.160
Which knife is suitable for cutting sashimi?

75
00:03:27.160 --> 00:03:29.280
Which pot is suitable for boiling soup?

76
00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:34.840
You just have to use this mentality to understand the temperament and ability of each AI tool in your hand.

77
00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:36.240
So here's the question.

78
00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:39.240
How do you establish this platform awareness?

79
00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:40.240
Let me tell you,

80
00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:41.960
there is no shortcut.

81
00:03:41.960 --> 00:03:43.760
Just one word, play.

82
00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:46.360
You just have to go down and try it yourself.

83
00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:50.960
If you play for a long time, you will find that some AI is really like a sports car.

84
00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:53.760
The speed is super fast, but it may not be so stable.

85
00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:57.200
Some of them are like a truck running slowly but very reliable.

86
00:03:57.200 --> 00:04:03.840
You can only find the tools that are most suitable for your work process by experiencing them yourself.

87
00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:08.240
Then slowly build your own AI weapon.

88
00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:10.120
OK, so you see,

89
00:04:10.120 --> 00:04:11.760
our platform is ready,

90
00:04:11.760 --> 00:04:13.440
we are familiar with the tools.

91
00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:16.760
Now we finally come to the most critical step.

92
00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:19.360
How do we smartly arrange our troops?

93
00:04:19.360 --> 00:04:21.680
That is, how to fail the task.

94
00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:27.040
I think this task is more like an art than a science.

95
00:04:27.040 --> 00:04:31.200
It's definitely not that you just throw your work to AI and it's fine.

96
00:04:31.200 --> 00:04:32.040
It's not.

97
00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:34.560
It's more like a conductor of a band.

98
00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:36.120
You have to be very clear.

99
00:04:36.120 --> 00:04:38.320
When should we let the violinist,

100
00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:39.520
that is, us humans,

101
00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:41.280
play a wonderful solo?

102
00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:43.320
When should we let the drummer,

103
00:04:43.320 --> 00:04:44.320
that is, AI,

104
00:04:44.320 --> 00:04:47.240
come out and drive the rhythm of the whole band?

105
00:04:47.240 --> 00:04:48.640
Hey, look at this picture.

106
00:04:48.640 --> 00:04:51.760
It makes this strategic division very clear.

107
00:04:51.760 --> 00:04:54.280
The left is the task that we humans are responsible for.

108
00:04:54.280 --> 00:04:56.360
You see, like what is the key judgment,

109
00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:57.560
strategic vision,

110
00:04:57.560 --> 00:05:00.080
and the most important responsibility.

111
00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:02.800
These tasks require high thinking and judgment.

112
00:05:02.800 --> 00:05:04.400
Of course, we still have to do it ourselves.

113
00:05:04.400 --> 00:05:07.320
The right is the task that is suitable for AI.

114
00:05:07.320 --> 00:05:09.480
For example, it takes a lot of time.

115
00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:11.040
It takes a lot of data to integrate,

116
00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:13.200
or some more routine interactions.

117
00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:14.160
So simply put,

118
00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:15.960
the rule is that we need to move our brains,

119
00:05:15.960 --> 00:05:17.720
and we need to be responsible for ourselves.

120
00:05:17.720 --> 00:05:19.760
Those more repetitive actions

121
00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:21.760
can be entrusted to AI.

122
00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:25.200
So you will find that the so-called tail is not actually

123
00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:28.240
a switch that gives or does not give.

124
00:05:28.240 --> 00:05:30.200
You can imagine it as a canvas.

125
00:05:30.200 --> 00:05:33.160
The end of the canvas is fully automated,

126
00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:35.640
allowing AI to process the whole process.

127
00:05:35.640 --> 00:05:37.560
In the middle, it may be strengthened,

128
00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:39.480
allowing AI to be your assistant,

129
00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:40.840
to strengthen your ability.

130
00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:42.040
Then there is the agent,

131
00:05:42.040 --> 00:05:44.480
allowing AI to help you deal with some complicated things.

132
00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:46.680
But the most important thing is

133
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:49.520
that you must have a clear red line in your heart,

134
00:05:49.520 --> 00:05:52.240
knowing that something is limited to humans.

135
00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:54.840
It is absolutely impossible to let go.

136
00:05:54.840 --> 00:05:58.120
Okay, let's quickly summarize here.

137
00:05:58.120 --> 00:06:01.840
So what should a really smart AI assistant

138
00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:04.440
look like?

139
00:06:04.440 --> 00:06:05.480
Today, the most important concept

140
00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:06.960
I think is this sentence.

141
00:06:06.960 --> 00:06:10.040
Don't just leave the canvas to AI.

142
00:06:10.040 --> 00:06:12.760
The real cooperation is you being the driver,

143
00:06:12.760 --> 00:06:16.200
and AI is the smartest navigation system around you.

144
00:06:16.200 --> 00:06:19.440
So your role must be transformed from a passive user

145
00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:23.520
to an active and strategic assistant.

146
00:06:23.520 --> 00:06:25.440
So after we finished talking today,

147
00:06:25.440 --> 00:06:27.920
I also want to leave a question for you to think about.

148
00:06:27.920 --> 00:06:29.760
In your next project,

149
00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:32.880
what kind of role are you going to let AI play?

150
00:06:32.880 --> 00:06:34.760
Is it just an obedient assistant?

151
00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:36.320
Or is it a convenient tool?

152
00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:38.680
Or can you improve it into

153
00:06:38.680 --> 00:06:41.800
a strategic partner who can work with you?

154
00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:43.840
I think how you answer this question

155
00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:47.200
will directly decide your future work outlook and efficiency.

156
00:06:47.200 --> 00:06:49.000
I hope the framework we talked about today

157
00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:51.200
can help you find your answer.

158
00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:52.360
Okay, that's it for today.

159
00:06:52.360 --> 00:06:53.200
Thank you for watching.

160
00:06:53.200 --> 00:06:54.200
See you next time.
